        <mxCell id="olovRQD_OqK5fJrkpe8d-119" parent="olovRQD_OqK5fJrkpe8d-1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;" value="There cannot be more water in the pipe than it can contain (water doesn&#39;t compact like gas does). When water reaches capacity in pipe, it&#39;s pressure becomes equal to the pumping engine incoming steam pressure * 0.7 (steam engine efficiency)." vertex="1">
